title: Yum Yum Spicy Chicken
desc: 6 Fried chicken pieces coated in a sweet & spicy sauce made from a blend of gochujang (Korean chili paste) & honey.

title: Tuna Kim-bap
desc: Tuna salad, lettuce, vegetables & seasoned rice wrapped in seaweed.

title: Dakgangjeong
desc: 6 fried chicken pieces coated in a sweet and tangy house marinade seasoned with garlic.

title: Vegetable Kim-bap
desc: Seasoned vegetables & rice wrapped in seaweed.

title: DolSot Yachae Bibimbap

title: Dubu Bokkeum
desc: Cubs of tofu sauteed with carrots, onions, mushrooms & bell peppers, served in our speacial seasoned soy sauce

title: Dolsot Bibimbap
desc: Beef, spinach, carrots, bean sprouts, shiitake mushrooms, zucchini & radish, each individually marinated. Served in a hot stone pot and topped with a fried egg. Comes with a side of gochujang sauce.

title: Ramen and Kimbap Set
desc: Choose between spicy OR mild ramen. Served with Yachae Kimbap & kimchi. Substitute for Chamchi Kimbap +$1.00.

title: Dakgalbi
desc: Chicken marinated in a gochujang sauce & cooked with cabbage, carrots, hot pepper & green onions. Served in a sizzling pan.

title: Dwaeji Bulgogi
desc: Thinly sliced marinated pork cooked with onions & green onions. Served in a sizzling pan

title: Bulgogi
desc: Thinly sliced beef cooked with onions, carrots, green onions & mushrooms. Served in a sizzling pan.

title: Tonkatsu
desc: Breaded deep-fried pork cutlet. Served with rice & choice of shredded lettuce with dressing OR macaroni salad & soup.

title: Chicken Nuggets
desc: Served with fresh fruit OR fries and regular drink of choice.

title: Mini Corn Dogs
desc: Served with fresh fruit OR fries and regular drink of choice.

title: Grill Cheese Sandwich & Fries
desc: Served with fresh fruit OR fries and regular drink of choice.

title: Dakgangjeong
desc: A crispy fried chicken dish that is coated in a sweet, sticky sauce, made with soy sauce, honey, garlic, and sesame oil, for a savory and slightly sweet flavor.

title: Oreo and Whipped Cream Croffle
desc: A new Korean dessert that combines croissants and waffles, topped with Oreo and whipped cream.

title: Biscoff + Strawberry & Whipped Cream Croffle
desc: A new Korean dessert that combines croissants and waffles, topped with Biscoff and whipped cream.

title: Strawberry and Whipped Cream Croffle
desc: A new Korean dessert that combines croissants and waffles, topped with Strawberry and whipped cream.

title: Nuttella and Whipped Cream Croffle
desc: A new Korean dessert that combines croissants and waffles, topped with Nuttella and whipped cream.

title: Bingsu With Fresh Fruit
desc: A refreshing treat made with finely shaved ice, topped with sweetened red beans, fresh fruit, condensed milk, and ice cream—perfect for cooling down after a spicy meal.

title: Melona Ice Cream
desc: A beloved Korean ice cream bark nown for its creamy texture and refreshing fruity taste. Hand made from melon-flavored cream encased in a thin colorful coating. Available in Melon, Strawberry and Mango

title: Ice Cream Soda
desc: A fun and fizzy beverage that’s a favorite among kids. It’s made by mixing lemon-lime soda with a scoop of ice cream, which creates a creamy and bubbly texture. Topped with a cherry and sprinkles for an extra treat.

title: Soji
desc: A traditional Korean distilled spirit, often compared to vodka but has a lower alcohol content and a smoother taste. Comes from rice, barley, sweet potatoes (distilled).

title: Makgeolli
desc: A traditional Korean rice wine made by fermenting rice, which results in a creamy and slightly sweet drink.

title: Binggrae Milk
desc: A beloved Korean drink, This sweet and creamy flavored milk is widely popular among children and adults alike. Flavors: Strawberry, Melon, Peach, Banana, Chocolate.

title: Iced Omija Tea
desc: A traditional Korean herbal tea made from the five-flavor berry (Omija). The drink is known for its sweet, sour, salty, bitter, and pungent flavors all at once. Served cold

title: Sikhye
desc: A sweet Korean rice drink made from fermented malt barley and cooked rice. Often enjoyed as a dessert.

title: Baekseju
desc: A traditional Korean herbal wine known for its medicinal properties, made from a blend of rice, ginseng, and other natural ingredients. The drink has a sweet and earthy flavor and is often consumed for health benefits.

title: Dongdongju
desc: This is a Korean unfiltered rice wine, similar to makgeolli but thicker and cloudier. It’s made by fermenting rice and barley. It has a slightly sweet and milky flavor.

title: Yogurt Soju
desc: Yogurt Soju is a sweet and smooth cocktail made by mixing soju with Yakult, a yogurt-based drink. It's very popular for those who prefer sweeter, milder cocktails.

title: Chamisul & Lemonade
desc: Chamisul is one of the most well-known soju brands in Korea. Mixed with lemonade for a refreshing, slightly tangy drink. This is a light and easy-to-drink cocktail

title: Soja Redbull
desc: This cocktail is a combination of Soju and Red Bull. This drink is served as a 'bomb' drink.The combination creates a sweet, energizing drink. *contains caffeine*

title: Cheese Burger & Fries
desc: A tasty and kid-friendly burger made with a juicy beef patty, melted cheese, and a soft bun, served with a side of crispy fries. No spicy ingredients, just delicious and cheesy goodness!

title: Fried Chicken Sliders
desc: Bite-sized crispy fried chicken coated in a sweet and spicy gochujang glaze, nestled in toasted slider buns with fresh pickles and a drizzle of our house creamy mayo. Paired with crispy fries.

title: Kimchi Grilled Cheese
desc: A fun twist on a classic. Gooey melted cheese with a little bit of tangy kimchi, all tucked between two slices of buttery, crispy bread. It's a cheesy, delicious snack paired with fresh fruit and choice of drink.

title: Gochujang BBQ Ribs
desc: Tender, slow-cooked ribs glazed in a sweet and spicy gochujang BBQ sauce. The perfect balance of heat and sweetness, served with a side of pickled radish and kimchi for the ultimate Korean BBQ experience.

title: Yuzu Soju Sour
desc: Our twist on the classic whiskey sour, this cocktail blends the bright, citrusy flavor of yuzu with smooth soju mixed with a dash of lemon juice, simple syrup, and egg white for a frothy finish.
